<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4608926>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 12. Megophrys oropedion from Meghalaya state, India: (a). adult male paratype (ZSI A 11602: SVL 33.9 mm) in life from Malki Forest, East Khasi Hills district; (b). adult female referred specimen (SDBDU 2009.299: SVL 48.7 mm) in life from Mawphlang Sacred Forest, East Khasi Hills district; (c). adult male (not collected) in life from Malki Forest, East Khasi Hills district; (d). subadult male (SDBDU 2007.310: SVL 32.1 mm) in life from Daribokgre, East Garo Hills district; (e–f). two adult males (left— SDBDU 2009.301: SVL 39.2 mm; right—SDBDU 2009.300: SVL 35.0 mm) and adult female (centre— SDBDU 2009.299: SVL 48.7 mm) referred specimens in preservation (not to scale) showing variation, from Mawphlang Sacred Forest, East Khasi Hills district: (e). dorsal view; (f). ventral view." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4608926/files/figure.png" .

